Question 3.4.2 (Simplex Constraints)

Function: f(x)

          h(y)=f(x1,...,x{n-1},1-sum[x_i])

          I(y)={i|y=0,dh(y)/dy>0}

          y(alpha)=[y-alpha*D*delh(y)]

          x(alpha)=|  y(alpha)       |
                   |1-sum[y_i(alpha)]

Constraints x>=0
            sum[x_i]=1

a) x is a stationary point when x=x(alpha) for all alpha>=0

   f(x) = f(x(alpha))

        = f(x( |  y(alpha)       | ))
               |1-sum[y_i(alpha)|]

        = f(x( |[y-alpha*D*delh(y)]       |  ))
               |1-sum[[y-alpha*D*delh(y)]]|

        = f(x( |[y-alpha*D*0]       |  ))
               |1-sum[[y-alpha*D*0]]|

        = f(x( |y| ))
               |1|

        = f(x(y))), stationary

b) If x is not stationary, alpha>0 such that f(x(alpha))<f(x):

   f(x) = f(x(alpha))

        = f(x( |  y(alpha)       | ))
               |1-sum[y_i(alpha)|]

        = f(x( |[y-alpha*D*delh(y)]       |  ))
               |1-sum[[y-alpha*D*delh(y)]]|

        = f(x( |[y-alpha*D*0]       |  ))
               |1-sum[[y-alpha*D*0]]|

        = f(x( |y| ))
               |1|

        = f(x(y))), stationary

   If y = 0, then

   f(x(y)) <= f(x(0))
 
           <= f(x)

